{"questionId":"9047814","questionHtml":"<p>The table shows the mRNA codons for three amino acids.</p>\n<table style=\"height:105px;\" border=\"1\" width=\"393\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Valine</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Threonine</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Proline</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\">GUU</td>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\">ACU</td>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\">CCU</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\">GCC</td>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\">ACC</td>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\">CCC</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\">GCA</td>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\">ACA</td>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\">CGA</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\">GCG</td>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\">ACG</td>\n<td style=\"width:124.162px;text-align:center;\">CCG</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Which substitution mutation of a base triplet on a DNA strand will lead to the same polypeptide being formed at translation?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; TGA to TCA</p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; CGT to CTA</p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; CAA to CGA</p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; GCT to GGA</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9047814","referenceCode":"SPM.1A.HL.TZ0.11","subjectId":"57-dp-biology-first-assessment-2025","title":"The table shows the mRNA codons for three amino acids. Valine Threonine Proline GUU ACU CCU GCC ACC CCC GCA ACA CGA GCG ACG CCG Which substitution mutation of a base triplet on a D","paper":"1A","level":"HL","questionNumber":"11","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["D. Continuity and Change","D. Continuity and Change","D1.3. Mutations and gene editing","D1.3.1. Gene mu